{{Merge to|College-preparatory school|date=August 2018}}

A '''College preparatory course''' is a means by which college bound high school students may better meet the more stringent scholastic requirements for entry into colleges and universities.<ref> [http://www.Stgregoryschool.org/about/why.html Stgregoryschool.org] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20080515223727/http://www.stgregoryschool.org/about/why.html |date=2008-05-15 }}, "Why St. Gregory?", accessed 02-06-2009</ref>  Students taking college-preparatory courses may have an increased quantity of classwork, and expectations to achieve are at a higher level.<ref> [http://www.collegeboard.com/ collegeboard.com], "College planning made easy", accessed 02-06-2009</ref>  The GPA (grade point average) weight for college-preparatory courses may have more value for college entry programs than regular courses.<ref name=edu1> [http://www.washington.edu/doit/Resources/college_prep.html washington.edu], "College Preparation Resources for Students ", accessed 02-06-2009</ref>  College prep courses are particularly appropriate for providing the academic background needed to succeed in a degree program at a college or university.<ref name=edu1/>  Above college-preparatory in difficulty is [[Honors course|honors]], where the advanced structure while similar in many ways to college prep, requires even more effort from the student.<ref>[http://www.uccp.org/] [[University of California]], "Welcome to UC College Prep, a statewide program of the University of California", accessed 02-06-2009</ref>  In many schools, a student can move from college-preparatory courses to [[Advanced Placement Program|Advanced Placement AP
]] courses, if they attain a certain average.<ref>[http://www.collegeboard.com/student/testing/ap/about.html collegeboard.com], "Advanced Placement Program", accessed 02-06-2009</ref>

