{{Infobox flag |Name = Ashanti |Nickname = {{nowrap|[[Asante dialect|Ashanti]] {{lang-tw|(Sika' dwa)}}}} |Image = Flag of Ashanti.svg |Use = 111000 |Proportion = 1:2 |Adoption = 1 January 1935 |Design = A horizontal [[tricolour (flag)|tricolour]] of [[gold (colour)|gold]], [[black (colour)|black]], [[green (colour)|green]] and [[White (colour)|white]] with the [[Golden Stool]] stationed in the middle of flag |Designer = [[Osei Kofi Tutu I|Emperor Osei Tutu I]] }}
The '''[[National flag|National Flag]] of [[Ashanti Region|Ashanti]]''' is the [[national flag]] of the [[Ashanti Region|Ashanti kingdom nation]], adopted by [[Ashanti Region|Ashanti kingdom nation]]'s [[List of rulers of Asante|Emperor Asantehene]] [[Osei Tutu Agyeman Prempeh II|Prempeh II]] in 1935, and is based on the [[List of rulers of Asante|Ashanti absolute monarchy]] [[throne]] the [[Golden Stool]], which has been the [[Ashanti people]]'s symbol of unity and [[sunsum]] (soul) since 1701 the early-eighteenth century [[Anno Domini|AD]] upon the foundation of the [[Ashanti Empire]].<ref name="Ashanti Golden Stool"/><ref name="Ashanti/Asante Stool"/><ref name="A First on Ashanti"/>
==History== The [[Golden Stool]] represents the Ashanti symbol of unity which is believed to possess the [[sunsum]] (soul) of the [[Ashanti people]].<ref name="Ashanti Golden Stool"/><ref name="Ashanti/Asante Stool"/><ref name="A First on Ashanti"/> In Ashanti legend, (the [[Golden Stool]]; Sika 'Dwa in the [[Asante dialect|Ashanti language]]) of the [[Ashanti people]]—descended from heaven in a cloud of white dust and landed in the lap of the first Ashanti [[List of rulers of Asante|Emperor Asantehene]] [[Osei Kofi Tutu I|Osei Tutu I]] in the late 1600s and was introduced onto the Ashanti flag by the [[List of rulers of Asante|Ashanti Emperor Asantehene]] [[Osei Tutu Agyeman Prempeh II|Prempeh II]] of [[Ashanti Region|Ashanti]] in taking the oath of the [[List of rulers of Asante|Ashanti absolute monarchy]] office [[Manhyia Palace]] upon the restoration of the [[Ashanti Region|Ashanti kingdom nation]] on 1 January 1935.<ref name="Ashanti Golden Stool"/><ref name="Ashanti/Asante Stool"/><ref name="A First on Ashanti"/> The national flag of Ashanti was created by emperor Asantehene [[Nana (title)|Nana]] [[Osei Tutu Agyeman Prempeh II|Prempeh II]] ([[Reign|r]]. 1935 – 1717).<ref name="Ashanti Golden Stool"/><ref name="Ashanti/Asante Stool"/><ref name="A First on Ashanti"/>
==Design and use== The national flag of [[Ashanti Region|Ashanti]] contains a [[gold (colour)|gold]] horizontal strip symbolizing the [[gold|gold mineral]] soil wealth and [[gold bar]] wealth of [[Ashanti Region|Ashanti]] and a [[Green (colour)|green]] horizontal strip representing the rich [[Ashanti Region|Ashanti nation]] [[rainforest]] [[ecozone]]; two thin-[[White (colour)|white]] horizontal strips and a [[Black (colour)|black]] horizontal strip surmounted by the [[Golden Stool]] (or [[Asante dialect|Ashanti]]: Sika' dwa) the unity symbol of the [[Ashanti people]] which has been the designated [[Ashanti Region|Ashanti kingdom nation]]'s national symbol of unity since 1701 into the present 21st century representing the [[Ashanti people]]'s drawing upon the Ashanti tradition of a stool indicating clan leadership, the [[Golden Stool]] became the symbol of the united [[Ashanti people]] and legitimized the rule of its possessor.<ref name="Ashanti Golden Stool"/><ref name="Ashanti/Asante Stool"/><ref name="A First on Ashanti"/> To defend the [[Golden Stool]] in 1900, the [[Ashanti people]] battled the English (British) in the so-called [[Ashanti Region|Ashanti kingdom nation]]'s [[Yaa Asantewa|Empress Ya Asantewaa]] [[War of the Golden Stool]] and [[List of rulers of Asante|Ashanti absolute monarchy]] [[throne]] protector of the [[Golden Stool]] and office [[Manhyia Palace]].<ref name="Ashanti Golden Stool">{{cite web|url=https://www.pbs.org/wonders/Episodes/Epi3/3_wond1a.htm|title=Ashanti Golden Stool|work=pbs.org}}</ref><ref name="Ashanti/Asante Stool">{{cite web|url=http://designblog.rietveldacademie.nl//wp-content/uploads/2008/03/viktorh_ashanti.pdf |title=Ashanti/Asante Stool|work=rietveldacademie.nl}}</ref><ref name="A First on Ashanti">{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=wlWh5hkw_YgC&pg=PA58&lpg=PA58&dq=ashanti+golden+stool+flag&source=bl&ots=ftayoXnwwY&sig=7sn0vuNxUU2MhzhbzLxy7PSuwYc&hl=en&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=ashanti%20golden%20stool%20flag&f=false|title=Black Lions: A First on Ashanti|author=Melvin F. Compton| work=Google Books}}</ref>
