]] |[[San Beda College]] |The father of Camaligan filed charges of murder against the fraternity members involved. The case was won with the paddle used in the hazing rite used as evidence.<ref>{{cite news|title=Reglos death saddens 1991 hazing victim kin|url=http://news.abs-cbn.com/video/nation/metro-manila/02/27/12/excl-reglos-death-saddens-1991-hazing-orphan|accessdate=6 October 2017|work=ABS-CBN News|date=27 February 2012|language=Filipino}}</ref> |- |{{dts|October 13, 1991}} | {{sortname|Frederick|Cahiyang|nolink=1}} |[[Alpha Phi Omega (Philippines)|Alpha Phi Omega]] |[[University of the Visayas]] |Reportedly the first publicized fatal hazing incident in [[Cebu]] schools.<ref>{{cite news|title=Cardinal Vidal Condemns Fraternity Hazing Death|url=https://www.ucanews.com/story-archive/?post_name=/1991/10/21/cardinal-vidal-condemns-fraternity-hazing-death&post_id=40039|accessdate=6 October 2017|work=UCNA News|date=21 October 1991}}</ref> |- |1991 | {{sortname|Felipe|Narne|nolink=1}} |{{N/A|No information}} |[[Araullo University]], [[Cabanatuan]] |<ref name="abs-cbn"/> |- |1992 | {{sortname|Joselito|Hernandez|nolink=1}} |Scintilla Juris |[[University of the Philippines Baguio]] |<ref name="abs-cbn"/> |- |{{dts|August 6, 1995}} | {{sortname|Mark Roland|Martin|nolink=1}} |Epsilon Chi |[[University of the Philippines Diliman]] |<ref name="gmaup"/> |- |{{dts|August 16, 1998}} | {{sortname|Alexander|Icasiano|nolink=1}} |Alpha Phi Beta |[[University of the Philippines Diliman]] |<ref>{{cite news|title=Ecunemical Protests Condemns Continued Hazing Deaths|url=https://www.ucanews.com/story-archive/?post_name=/1998/08/27/ecumenical-protest-condemns-continued-fraternity-hazing-deaths&post_id=12018|accessdate=6 October 2017|work=UCNA News|date=27 August 1998}}</ref><ref>[http://osu.up.edu.ph/wp-content/uploads/gazette/1998.pdf UP Gazette 1998]</ref> |- |}
