==Notable contemporary techno venues==

[[File:Berghain in October 2014.jpg|upright=0.9|thumb|right|The world-famous Berghain techno club]]

[[Berghain]] night club in Berlin, famed for its no-holds-barred revelry and 24 hour opening policy, is considered by many to be the "world capital" of techno.<ref name="Pitch1">{{cite web|url=http://pitchfork.com/features/techno/6604-techno/ |title = The Month In: Techno |date=2007-05-09 |last  = Sherburne |first = Philip |work = [[Pitchfork Media]] |accessdate=2007-07-04}}</ref> Other notable Berlin venues include Tresor and Watergate. In the [[United Kingdom]]  Glasgow's [[Sub Club]] has been associated with techno since the early 1990s and clubs such as London's [[Fabric (club)|Fabric]] and [[Egg London]] have gained notoriety for supporting techno.<ref>{{cite web|author=Timeout Magazine |url=https://www.timeout.com/london/clubs/egg-london|title=Egg London |publisher=Timeout.com|date=2012-06-20}}</ref><ref name=djmag>{{cite web|author=DJ Mag |url=https://djmag.com/top-100-clubs/poll-clubs-2017-egg-london |title=Egg London |publisher=djmag.com|date=2017-12-20}}</ref>

